# Keep the docs in sync — always

When you change behavior, update the affected docs **in the same session**. Docs
must never drift from reality.

## Update targets

- **`README.md`** — user-facing overview / run / features. **Always** review and
  update it for anything user-visible.
- **`CONTEXT.md`** — living detailed context (see the context-file rule).
- **`AGENTS.md`** — project guide: conventions, file tree, and the **"Done
  recently"** list. Add new files to the tree.
- **`AUDIT.md` / `AUDIT2.md`** — if the change touches something audited
  (security, concurrency, financial correctness), update its remediation status.

## Roadmap — where it lives

The roadmap is tracked in **`AGENTS.md`** under **"Roadmap / ideas (not yet
built)"** and **"Futures roadmap"**, and mirrored in **`README.md`** and
**`CONTEXT.md`**. When you **finish** a roadmap item, mark it done and move a note
to "Done recently"; when a **new idea** comes up, add it to the roadmap. Keep all
three copies consistent.

If unsure which doc, at minimum update `README.md` **and** `CONTEXT.md`.
